The paper discusses learning reward functions for robots, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on interpreting human behavior as evidence of the reward function, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses how humans make choices based on rewards, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and control systems (cs.SY).
